                <h1>Tracing Central Basin's trust fund</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="text collapse">
                <p><span class="credits">Produced by <a href="http://www.scpr.org/about/people/staff/karen-foshay">Karen Foshay</a> & <a href="http://www.scpr.org/about/people/staff/chris-keller">Chris Keller</a></span> | <span class="pubdate">Published Dec. 20, 2013</span></p>
                <p>The FBI is investigating what happened to $2.7 million the Central Basin Municipal Water District put into a trust fund to create an environmental impact report for a water storage project.  The money has also been the subject of questions from one of the district’s board members and been described by another as a slush fund. Documents obtained by KPCC highlight some of the saga’s unanswered questions.</p>
